WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.700
That is the name of the main hall of the museum, containing mural paintings telling us the

00:04.700 --> 00:10.360
glorious victory which lasted for 25 years under Skanderbeg's leadership.

00:10.360 --> 00:14.640
The mural paintings are recounting for the following events.

00:14.640 --> 00:21.920
After the Battle of Nish, November 3, 1443, Skanderbeg together with 300 Albanian northern

00:21.920 --> 00:29.620
horsemen returned in Kruja where on November 28, 1443, the red Albanian flag with the double-headed

00:29.620 --> 00:31.740
eagle was risen.

00:31.740 --> 00:36.760
In the painting, our national hero is presented knelt before his mother and a swell as a part

00:36.760 --> 00:39.940
of his speech held in front of the people of Kruja saying,

00:39.940 --> 00:44.920
I was not the one who brought you freedom, I found it here among you.

00:44.920 --> 00:50.000
The unification under the leadership of Skanderbeg was decided in Leja.

00:50.000 --> 00:55.380
Here one can find displayed also the flags of the main princedoms, castriots, skorais,

00:55.740 --> 01:04.740
The mural painting in the center of the room is featuring fragments from the Albanian-Ottoman

01:04.740 --> 01:06.460
Wars.

01:06.460 --> 01:13.780
This painting is the biggest in our country, about 108 square meters and contains 300 characters.

01:13.780 --> 01:20.360
The author of this gigantic painting is Najib Akali, who worked for about 11 and half months.

01:20.360 --> 01:25.140
In the same room are exhibited the sword and spiky helmet of Skanderbeg, the original are

01:25.140 --> 01:27.940
in Vienna Museum of Arms.

01:27.940 --> 01:32.300
For 25 years Skanderbeg fought over 20 battles.

01:32.300 --> 01:40.100
The most prominent ones are the Third Kruja Sieges in 1450, in 1466 and in 1467, the Battle

01:40.100 --> 01:49.460
of Torvjali in 1444, the Battle of Albulin in 1457, and the Battle of Vaikali in 1465.

01:49.460 --> 01:53.700
This painting shows the last moments of Skanderbeg's life.

01:53.700 --> 01:58.900
Here are presented the tearful warriors and at the same time unified.

01:58.900 --> 02:03.900
Skanderbeg died in Leja on January 17 in 1467.

02:03.900 --> 02:08.780
With his activity, Skanderbeg takes the most important place in Albanian history and he

02:08.780 --> 02:11.220
is our national hero.

02:11.220 --> 02:17.300
In alabaster are shown some of the main fortresses from the Middle Ages, Barati, Petrela, Rodon

02:17.300 --> 02:19.900
and the fortress of Kruja.

02:19.900 --> 02:24.060
In the map is shown a wider distribution of the fortifications while the engravings on

02:24.060 --> 02:28.260
the side are demonstrating moments from the four battles.

02:28.260 --> 02:33.060
The engraving on glass features the First Kruja Siege by the Ottomans in 1450.

